---
title: Hot Smoked Salmon Orzo with Charred Courgette and Chilli
description: Velvety and comforting, our hot smoked salmon orzo recipe is the perfect recipe for chillier evenings. When the orzo pasta is nearly done (it should slightly retain its bite) stir in our delicious smoked salmon with the zest of a lemon and Italian cheese and serve everything up. Enjoy!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/hot-smoked-salmon-orzo-e54191b8-19129a8a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/hot-smoked-salmon-orzo-5ef3470e777efd03105e9c0e-ea10adc5.pdf
author: Mimi Morley
servings: 2
cuisine: Italian
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 638 kcal
  fat: 16 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 39 g
  sodium: 3 g
  serving size: 472
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/hot-smoked-salmon-orzo-5ef3470e777efd03105e9c0e
---

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Trim the @courgette{1} then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lemon{1}, thinly slice the @red chilli{1/2}.

Put a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Once the pan is hot, add the courgette and cook until nicely charred, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn every ~{2%minutes}. Remove to a #bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Don't wash the pan.

Put your frying pan back on the heat and reduce the heat to medium. Add a drizzle of @oil{} and the onion, fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add a drizzle of oil at this point if the pan is dry.

Add the @orzo{180%g} to the pan and stir to coat in the oil, then pour in the @water{450%ml} and the @vegetable stock powder{1%portion}. Bring to the boil and simmer until the orzo is tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Stir every couple of mins to ensure the orzo isn't sticking to the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if it's not cooked through and the liquid has evaporated.

When the orzo is cooked, add the @baby spinach{125%g} in handfuls and stir through to wilt. Stir through the @hot smoked salmon{150%g} and cook until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat, add the lemon zest and three quarters of the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated). Stir together, then taste and add salt, pepper and lemon juice if you feel it needs it. Stir in half the courgette.

Serve the orzotto in bowls with the remaining courgette and cheese sprinkled on top. Finish with the slices of chilli and a good grind of pepper. Cut the remaining lemon into wedges and serve alongside, enjoy!